{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"InvertedPendulum","roleHeading":"Class","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Gym"}],"externalID":"s:3Gym16InvertedPendulumC","symbolKind":"class"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Env","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/MuJoCoEnv"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":3,"text":"Description","type":"heading","anchor":"Description"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This environment is the cartpole environment based on the work done by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Barto, Sutton, and Anderson in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ieeexplore.ieee.org\/document\/6313077","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"just like in the classic environments but now powered by the Mujoco physics simulator -","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allowing for more complex experiments (such as varying the effects of gravity).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This environment involves a cart that can moved linearly, with a pole fixed on it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at one end and having another end free. The cart can be pushed left or right, and the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"goal is to balance the pole on the top of the cart by applying forces on the cart.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Action Space","type":"heading","anchor":"Action-Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The agent take a 1-element vector for actions."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The action space is a continuous "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(action)"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[-3, 3]"},{"type":"text","text":", where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"action"},{"type":"text","text":" represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the numerical force applied to the cart (with magnitude representing the amount of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"force and sign representing the direction)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Min"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Max"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Joint","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Force applied on the cart","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-3"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slider"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Force (N)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"level":3,"text":"Observation Space","type":"heading","anchor":"Observation-Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The state space consists of positional values of different body parts of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pendulum system, followed by the velocities of those individual parts (their derivatives)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with all the positions ordered before all the velocities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The observation is a "},{"code":"ndarray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with shape "},{"code":"(4,)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" where the elements correspond to the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Num"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Observation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Min"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Max","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Joint","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"position of the cart along the linear surface"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slider"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"position (m)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"vertical angle of the pole on the cart"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"angle (rad)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"linear velocity of the cart"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slide"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"velocity (m\/s)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"angular velocity of the pole on the cart"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"anglular velocity (rad\/s)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"level":3,"text":"Rewards","type":"heading","anchor":"Rewards"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The goal is to make the inverted pendulum stand upright (within a certain angle limit)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as long as possible - as such a reward of +1 is awarded for each timestep that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the pole is upright.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Starting State","type":"heading","anchor":"Starting-State"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All observations start in state","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0) with a uniform noise in the range","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of [-0.01, 0.01] added to the values for stochasticity.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Episode End","type":"heading","anchor":"Episode-End"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The episode ends when any of the following happens:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Truncation: The episode duration reaches 1000 timesteps.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: Any of the state space values is no longer finite."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: The absolutely value of the vertical angle between the pole and the cart is greater than 0.2 radian."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":3,"text":"Arguments","type":"heading","anchor":"Arguments"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No additional arguments are currently supported.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["env = gym.make('InvertedPendulum-v4')"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There is no v3 for InvertedPendulum, unlike the robot environments where a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"v3 and beyond take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Version History","type":"heading","anchor":"Version-History"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks (including inverted pendulum)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/init()"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/data","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/model"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/Env-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/gym","kind":"symbol","title":"Gym","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym"},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/InvertedPendulum":{"title":"InvertedPendulum","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}]},"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/6313077":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Neuronlike adaptive elements that can"},{"type":"text","text":" 